Detailed Description

High level Magnetic Field Mapper (MFM) management class.

Most functions return a boolean indicating success, a null-object, empty lists or nothing at all. In some cases more in-depth knowledge of the error is required (

See Also
loadInputFile). Therefore they return an XsResultValue
Note
This object cannot be copied. The copy constructor has been disabled.

XsResultValue XsMfm::loadInputFile ( const XsString &  inputFile,
const XsDeviceId &  deviceId,
XsDeviceId &  detectedDeviceId 
)
inline

Load a file which contains a magnetic field mapping movement.

Parameters
inputFileThe mtb file that contains the magnetic field mapping recording
deviceIdThe live device of which inputFile contains a recording
detectedDeviceIdThe device ID which was found in the file
Returns
  • XRV_OK The file is ok,
  • XRV_UNEXPECTEDMSG The file does not contain the required data
  • XRV_UNSUPPORTED The file is from a different motion tracker then deviceId
  • XRV_NULLPTR There is no device found in the log file
XsResultValue XsMfm::loadInputFile ( const XsStringArray &  inputFileArray,
const XsDeviceIdArray &  deviceIdArray,
XsDeviceIdArray &  detectedDeviceIdArray 
)
inline

Loads files which contain a magnetic field mapping movement.

Parameters
inputFileArrayAn array of mtb files that contain magnetic field mapping recordings
deviceIdArrayThe matching array of live devices of which inputFileArray contains the recordings
detectedDeviceIdArrayThe array of device IDs which were found in the files
Returns
  • XRV_OK The file is ok,
  • XRV_UNEXPECTEDMSG The file does not contain the required data
  • XRV_UNSUPPORTED The file is from a different motion tracker then deviceId
  • XRV_NULLPTR There is no device found in the log file
